<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of
tonight's New York Times Photo Package, moving Tuesday, 08/01/00.
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
213-237-4577 or PressLink at 800-888-6195. Non-clients can make
individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT36) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 1, 2000 -- GOP-RDP-15 --
Condoleezza Rice, Gov. George W. Bush's chief international affairs
adviser, speaking to the Republican National Convention, Tuesday.
Rice, who as an African American, underscores Bush's pledge to put
minorities in consequential roles, cited Bush as a man of uncommonly
good judgment. "He is focused and consistent. He believes that we
Americans are at our best when we exercise power without fanfare or
arrogance and he speaks plainly with a positive spirit," Rice said.
(Andrea Mohin/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT35) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 1, 2000 -- GOP-RDP-14 -- A group
of delegates from Texas listen to their governor George W. Bush
speaking to the Republican National Convention via a satellite
hookup, Tuesday. For the second straight night, Bush addressed the
delegates from the campaign trail, this time from Gettysburg, Pa., in
front of a desk once owned by President Dwight Eisenhower. (Chang W.
Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT34) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 1, 2000 -- GOP-RDP-13 -- A group
of delegates from Texas cheer on their governor George W. Bush
speaking to the Republican National Convention via a satellite
hookup, Tuesday. For the second straight night, Bush addressed the
delegates from the campaign trail, this time from Gettysburg, Pa., in
front of a desk once owned by President Dwight Eisenhower. Bush will
arrive in Philadelphia Wednesday in a newly decorated Boeing 727
painted red, white and blue with the American flag and BUSH-CHENEY
emblazoned on the side. (Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT33) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 1, 2000 -- GOP-RDP-12 -- John
McCain, who fought a fierce primary battle with George W. Bush last
spring, took the spotlight at the Republican National Convention,
Tuesday to praise his former foe as a leader of "courage and
character" who would restore U.S. prestige abroad. The endorsement by
the former Navy pilot, who was shot down in Vietnam and spent 5 1/2
years in a Vietnamese prison camp, provides added luster for Bush on
military issues. (Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT32) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 1, 2000 -- GOP-RDP-11 -- A group
of delegates from Texas applaud former President Gerald R. Ford
during his speech at the Republican National Convention, Tuesday.
(Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
