congressman and secretary of defense, along with his granddaughter
during the second session of the Republican National Convention,
Tuesday. Cheney and George W. Bush plan a campaign swing by train
through Ohio, Michigan and Illinois on Friday, after the convention.
President Clinton won each state handily in 1996. (Ruth Fremson/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 1, 2000 -- GOP-RDP-8 -- As the
GOP convention band played "Devil with a Blue Dress," Barbara Bush
took the stage at the Republican National Convention, Tuesday, and
introduced her son George W., appearing by satellite from nearby
Gettysburg, Pa. "I hope I am the first person to welcome you to
Philadelphia, the city of motherly love," she said, a twist on the
"brotherly" love for which the city likes to be known. (Ruth
Fremson/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
