   (NYT27) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 1, 2000 -- GOP-RDP-6 -- Eyes
glistening, Bob Dole speaking during the second session of the
Republican National Convention, Tuesday on behalf of hundreds of
thousands of "voiceless heroes" who never came home from wars. Dole
said that wearing this nation's uniform in battle was a grater honor
than winning his party's presidential nomination. In paying tribute
to his comrades in arms, Dole, 77, also hailed young Americans,
"heroes in waiting."  (Andrea Mohin/The New York Times)
