<P>
   (NYT20) NEW KENSINGTON, Pa.  -- Aug.1,  2000 -- HONEST-TEA-2
-- Seth Goldman and Barry Nalebuff started Honest Tea two years ago,
to fill what they saw as a neglected market niche. Well aware that
they would be competing against mass-marketed sweetened iced teas
made by their competitors, Goldman and Naalebuff wanted to make an
iced tea that promoted natural tea flavor. Their tea leaves are high
quality and expensive. George Scalf, a brew master, working on a
batch of Honest Tea at the company's plant in New Kensington, Pa.
(Gary Tramontina/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) WASHINGTON -- Aug.1,  2000 -- HONEST-TEA-1 -- Seth
Goldman, foreground, and Barry Nalebuff started Honest Tea two years
ago, to fill what they saw as a neglected market niche. Well aware
