   (NYT18) HOUSTON -- Aug. 1, 2000 --
MUSIC-LIMPBIZKIT-REVIEW-HNS -- For 2,500 Limp Bizkit fans, Monday
night in Houston, Texas, the political and legal ramifications of
online music, and the future of music distribution involving Napster
certainly played out in their favor. Many of Limp Bizkit's
performances are being underwritten by Napster, the online music
download site supported by Limp Bizket, and are free for their fans.
Limp Bizkit lead singer Fred Durst performing during the first of the
band's free shows on Monday at the Aerial Theater. (Dave Rossman/The
Houston Chronicle)
</P>
