"Becoming Madame Mao" has been popping up on bestseller lists in San
Francisco, Los Angeles, and Boston, tells the tale of Jiang Ching,
the wife of Chinese communist leader Mao Tze-tung.  In her boosk,
Anchee Min upgrades Jiang Ching from "demon" to human, if a scheming,
murderous one. Anchee during a recent interview in Boston.  (Suzanne
Kreiter/The Boston Globe)
