<HEADLINE>
AFTER CONVENTION SESSION, FORD IS TAKEN TO HOSPITAL 
</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA _ Former President Gerald Ford was taken to
Hahnemann University Hospital on Tuesday night with an unspecified
illness.
</P>
<P>
   Ford, 87, apparently was driven to the hospital in Center City
after Tuesday night's session of the Republican Convention, where
he was celebrated along with other former Republcian presidents.
</P>
<P>
   Ford, sitting along side his wife, Betty, appeared frail and was
visibly moved when a video-taped tribute to him was displayed on
the large screens inside the First Union Center here. He rose and
waved to acknowledge the cheers.
</P>
<P>
   He spent the night sitting in a VIP box at the back of the hall
along with Former President George Bush, Nancy Reagan, Bob Dole and
other prominent Republicans. Although Ford did not address the
crowd he told C-Span earlier that this would be the last convention
he would attend.
</P>
</TEXT>
