   GOP-FUNDRAISING (Philadelphia) _ Republican officials insist
that their financial base is primarily small donors, but the party
has received more than $90 million from a relatively small pool of
wealthy individuals and corporations, some of whom have shielded
their generosity from public view. By Don Van Natta Jr. and John M.
Broder.
