   GOP-ASSESS (Philadelphia) _ Tuesday night, for the second night
in a row, one of the principal speakers at the Republican National
Convention was a black person. Tuesday night, it was Condoleezza
Rice, the chief national security adviser to Gov. George W. Bush of
Texas; on Monday night, it was Colin Powell, who may be secretary
of state if Bush is elected president. Obviously, this was no
happenstance. In this convention, whose sole mission is the
glorification of Bush, happenstance just doesn't happen. By R.W.
Apple Jr.
