<P>
   DISPOSABLE-PAPER-PANS (Undted0 _ It's a wonder no one ever
thought of it before. For years commercial bakers have baked their
pies and tarts, their pannetones and sweet breads in disposable
paper pans. That saves them thousands of miles of shelving that
would otherwise be crammed with aluminum foil pans. Now these paper
pans are becoming more available to home bakers, who have even
tighter space constraints. Made of specially treated paper, the
pans come in all shapes, including Bundt, are inexpensive and are
actually rather attractive, with gold and silver designs embossed
on a brown background. By Marian Burros.
