<P>
   MEDIGAP (Phoenix) - Premiums for Medicare supplemental insurance
in Arizona often are two times more expensive as the premiums paid
by seniors in other states. Premium costs can vary widely from
state to state, city to city and insurer to insurer on identical
policies for the same individual, says a survey of premium costs by
Weiss Ratings Inc. We look at premium rates for Arizona and try to
explain the disparity in costs. By DELLA DE LAFUENTE. Story will
move in the ``A'' category.
</P>
<P>
   PBS {ndash}(Phoenix) - PBS stations around the country are
airing an award-winning documentary about urban sprawl. Part of it
was shot in the Phoenix area, and two high-profile Valley residents
-- sports baron Jerry Colangelo and architect Vern Swabach -- are
featured. But the Valley's PBS station, KAET-TV, Channel 8, says
``Subdivide and Conquer'' isn't balanced enough to show before the
November election, when controversial growth-related measures are
on the ballot. Supporters of the Citizens Growth Management
Initiative say the debate is exactly why the public needs to see
this film. By KATHLEEN INGLEY. Story will move in the ``A''
category.
</P>
<P>
   ROBB (Philadelphia) - The Republican platform adopted by
convention delegates without discussion or dissent on Monday closes
two important chapters in Republican conservatism: a commitment to
rollback the mission of the federal government, and a commitment to
growth-oriented tax cuts as the anchor of domestic policy. By
Robert Robb column. Story will move on the ``K'' wire.
</P>
