we think we are doing.''
</P>
<P>
   But it is also a myth that only at Camp David did the issue of
Jerusalem first get an airing. It was certainly the first time it
was broached directly at the very top, but Jerusalem has been under
discussion for quite a while. Yossi Beilin, a senior minister in
Barak's government, negotiated Jerusalem's future with Abu Mazen, a
senior Palestinian official, in 1995. The Rabin assassination in
November of that year ended those discussions.
</P>
<P>
   There are many reasons for pessimism over the Israeli-Arab
conflict. There is a huge disparity in culture and income and
