electrocardiograms to detect the treatable heart problem, which may
account for 10 to 30 percent of the 2,800 sudden infant deaths a
year. But most American experts oppose routine electrocardiograms,
saying they would not save enough lives to justify the expense.
</P>
<P>
   _ By DENISE GRADY
</P>
