Wireless Corp., for $50.7 billion. The deal caught the attention of
more than two dozen legislators in Washington, who have written to
the chairman of the Federal Communications Commission seeking to
block the acquisition because Deutsche Telekom's majority
shareholder is the German government.
</P>
<P>
   _ By ANDREW ROSS SORKIN
</P>
<P>
   Charges of IRS Corruption
</P>
<P>
   At least five of eight suspended IRS tax collectors, auditors
