The Compact Oxford English Dictionary, New Edition shows the Latin
word has been used by English speakers as meaning seriousness or
sobriety of conduct, bearing, speech or temperament; weighty
dignity; reverend seriousness or serious or solemn conduct.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I always thought that Australia had seasons opposite to ours,
