grown nearly 500 percent in the past five years, generating nearly
$5.7 billion in revenue last year, according to a new survey. By
ALAN T. SARACEVIC.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   OLY-SWIM (San Francisco) _ In 1992, Angie Wester-Krieg was
described as ``the Grande Dame of U.S. Swimming.'' It's hard to say
what that makes her now. At 35, Wester-Krieg is still swimming.
Very well, in fact. She has qualified for her sixth U.S. Olympic
trials, which is a record as far as USA Swimming officials can
determine. By DWIGHT CHAPIN.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL (``t'' category)
</P>
<P>
   TRAV-OZARKS _ LAKE OF THE OZARKS, Mo. _ Here's a tip for those
who make regular pilgrimages to Branson, mid-America's most popular
parking lot: Next visit, once you've seen all the Osmonds and
Lennons _ no small accomplishment _ and escaped the traffic
gridlock on 76 Country Boulevard, mosey up the road about 21/2
hours and into a different world. By HARRY SHATTUCK
W/TRAV-OZARKS-TIPS.
</P>
<P>
   TRAV-FREE-ORLANDO _ With theme park ticket prices inching toward
the $50 per day mark, vacationers to central Florida could use some
inexpensive diversions. Here are 10 free Orlando-area attractions
that can help stretch the family travel budget. By SYD KEARNEY.
</P>
<P>
   TRAV-FREE-STLOUIS _ Ten free attractions for visitors to St.
Louis. By SYD KEARNEY.
</P>
<P>
   TRAV-FREE-SANFRANCISCO _ Ten free attractions for visitors to
San Francisco. By SYD KEARNEY
</P>
