<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LONESOMEDOVE-RECIPES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
RECIPES FROM LONESOME DOVE WESTERN BISTRO
</HEADLINE>
 
 (EDS: Accompanies RESTAURANT-LONESOME DOVE)  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Recipes from Lonesome Dove Western Bistro, Tim Love, chef/owner
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   WESTERN PLAID HASH
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   1 cup potatoes, cut in thin strips
</P>
<P>
   Peanut oil
</P>
<P>
   1 cup green cabbage, cut in thin strips
</P>
<P>
   1/2 red onion, cut in thin strips
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup jalapenos, chopped
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup sweet red peppers, cut in thin strips
</P>
<P>
   2 cloves garlic
</P>
<P>
   Salt and pepper, to taste
</P>
<P>
   Olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup Penfolds Kanoonga Hill Cabernet/Shiraz
</P>
<P>
   1 cup reduced beef stock
</P>
<P>
   Fry potatoes in 350-degree peanut oil.
</P>
<P>
   Saute cabbage, onions, peppers, and garlic with a touch of salt
and pepper in olive oil.
</P>
<P>
   Add wine and simmer for a minute.
</P>
<P>
   Add beef stock and toss; pour over fried potatoes.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 149 calories, 11 grams fat, 11
grams carbohydrates, 2 grams protein, trace cholesterol, 20
milligrams sodium, 65 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   ASIAN STIR-FRY VEGETABLES
</P>
<P>
   Serves 4
</P>
<P>
   1/8 cup olive oil
</P>
<P>
   1 cup shiitake mushrooms, stems removed
</P>
<P>
   1 cup napa cabbage
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup red peppers, julienned
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup red onion, julienned
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup yellow squash, julienned
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup zucchini squash, julienned
</P>
<P>
   1/4 cup mirin, see Note
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup Thai vinaigrette, recipe follows
</P>
<P>
   Note: Mirin is a low-alcohol rice wine available at liquor
stores and Asian markets.
</P>
<P>
   Heat olive oil. Add all vegetables. Add mirin and reduce, then
add Thai vinaigrette and bring to boil.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per serving: 206 calories, 17 grams fat, 13
grams carbohydrates, 3 grams protein, trace cholesterol, 141
milligrams sodium, 72 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Thai vinaigrette:
</P>
<P>
   Yields 3 cups
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup honey
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup hoisin sauce
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup chopped cilantro
</P>
<P>
   2 cloves garlic
</P>
<P>
   1 cup rice wine vinegar
</P>
<P>
   1/2 cup sesame seeds
</P>
<P>
   1 cup olive oil
</P>
<P>
   In a food processor, combine all ingredients except oil and
pulse until well-combined. With machine running, slowly add oil.
</P>
<P>
   Nutritional analysis per tablespoon: 64 calories, 5 grams fat, 4
grams carbohydrates, 1 gram protein, trace cholesterol, 66
milligrams sodium, 77 percent of calories from fat.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
