<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ Orchids really have a hold on me. It's been a
while since I've been in an orchid period, about five or six years.
Like many orchid dabblers, I'd enjoy the blooms for months and then
I'd watch the plants just sit there for the next year or so. Now, I
have returned to orchids with zeal, if not skill. So go the rhythms
of gardening. You embrace a plant, then you let it go, returning to
embrace it again, perhaps years later. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CUT-CORNERS _ ATLANTA _ Jackie Cottrill of Atlanta knows how to
cut corners _ and, more importantly, when not to. After all, she
has decorated and designed, 18 houses for her family over the last
25 years. Yet she's not a professional designer or decorator; she's
a homemaker who's learned dozens of tricks of the trade by working
closely with architects, builders and other experts. Story
includes: 12 decorating and designing tips, Cottrill's bargain
shops and money-saving hints. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) WITH PHOTOS.
