<P>
   NEWS-QUESTIONS _ Q&AMP;A on the news, in two takes. (Bessonette,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) (EDS: Moving on l (Lifestyle) and a
(General News) categories.) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   HOME AND GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   NUTSNBOLTS _ There seemed to be fireplace inserts and wood
stoves everywhere during the 1970s and 1980s. More recently
high-tech gas fireplaces seem to be dominant.
</P>
<P>
   This week we answer a question from a family that has gotten rid
of its old fireplace insert. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News). 27.
</P>
<P>
   GARDENING-LIFE _ Orchids really have a hold on me. It's been a
while since I've been in an orchid period, about five or six years.
Like many orchid dabblers, I'd enjoy the blooms for months and then
I'd watch the plants just sit there for the next year or so. Now, I
have returned to orchids with zeal, if not skill. So go the rhythms
of gardening. You embrace a plant, then you let it go, returning to
embrace it again, perhaps years later. (May, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CUT-CORNERS _ ATLANTA _ Jackie Cottrill of Atlanta knows how to
cut corners _ and, more importantly, when not to. After all, she
has decorated and designed, 18 houses for her family over the last
25 years. Yet she's not a professional designer or decorator; she's
a homemaker who's learned dozens of tricks of the trade by working
closely with architects, builders and other experts. Story
includes: 12 decorating and designing tips, Cottrill's bargain
shops and money-saving hints. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   CONSUMER NEWS
</P>
<P>
   BUYER'S-EDGE _ We go waaay beyond pencils and paper as we take a
look at cool things to get you through school with the latest
trends from colorful calculators to a TV on a rope to stash in your
bookbag _ plus a personal CD player, neon floppy disks and funky
timepieces you can clip to your bookbag or wear around your neck.
(Morrow, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-GUIDE _ A weekly feature telling how to locate
hard-to-fnd items. This week: Maypo, maple oatmeal, Baron men's
cologne and Red Rooster Hot Sause. (Johnson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   SHOPPING-DESTINATION _ A weekly feature about fun places to shop
in the Southeast. This week: Hartwell, Ga., where you'll find
mountains, a lake and a lively downtown, (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
