   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet FOOD page for the current week. This
layout is available now.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET FOOD 0729: LEMONADE STAND -- We asked them and other
grown-up experts how to build, market, staff and run the perfect,
profitable lemonade stand here are a collection of ideas to make
your lemonade stand tops in the neighborhoo. (Sturrock, Palm Beach
Post) Art includes a 3-column color illustration of a menu and
business plan for a lemonade stand.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BEER CAN CHICKEN -- Chicken is rarely the first thing that comes
to my mind when I think of firing up the grill. Chicken? Boring. At
least that's what I thought until beer changed my mind. Or more
precisely a beer can. With recipe for Coca-Cola Barbecue Sauce.
(Walker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 1-column
color photo of a chef preparing beer-can chicken.
</P>
<P>
   IN PRINT -- How many food experts could possibly write a
cookbook titled ``From My Chateau Kitchen'' and expect to be taken
seriously? Would anyone not fortunate enough to live in a chateau
be able to duplicate the recipes? (Fabricant, N.Y. Times News
Service) Art includes a 1-column color photo of book jacket.
</P>
