be used only once, such as catheters, to pass new safety tests. The
regulations will apply to companies that clean and repackage the
devices for subsequent use, and to hospitals that do this work
themselves. Under the regulations, they must demonstrate that the
recycled devices meet the same standards as new devices do. By
Kenneth Chang.
