<HEADLINE>
H2-OH! COOL SUMMER WATER TOYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SANDY GUERRA-CLINE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Buy summer water toys now? You betcha. A good bit of summer
weather still stretches ahead of us like a heat mirage on a
four-lane highway.
</P>
<P>
   Besides, you can get great deals on water toys right now. Stores
_ especially the big discount stores _ are turning their attention
to layaway-till-Christmas prospects, so you can find entire aisles
of discounted water toys. What doesn't get used in the next month
or two can be stashed in the garage until next summer. And your
kids will be on very good behavior when they know you have a
plastic water cannon tucked away in the hall closet. (Of course,
smart parents would never give up the location of their toy stash
... even under threat of water-toy torture.)
</P>
<P>
   Here are five of our favorite backyard water toys, for all
swimsuit sizes, no swimming pool required:
</P>
<P>
   1. Super Soaker Big Trouble by Larami: Your child has probably
whined for this one: a water gun with a backpack reservoir for
extended water battles that promises ``fast refills and super
firepower.'' Kid testers for Zillions, Consumer Reports for Kids,
gave it an ``excellent'' rating but noted that the 8-pound pack can
get too heavy for smaller kids. Our 7-year-old tester, 50 pounds
soaking wet, had no such trouble, wreaking a lot of havoc on his
older sisters. Suggested retail price: $30 (but we scored one at
Wal-Mart last week for $19.95).
</P>
<P>
   2. Super Soaker Splashketball by Playskool: Basketball with
splashy rewards; cyber toy store etoys.com recommends this backyard
game for kiddos ages 3 to 6, but older kids certainly can work on
their hand-eye coordination and have just as much fun getting wet.
Doesn't require anything more than the garden hose. Suggested
retail price: $10.
</P>
<P>
   3. SuperSpiral Sprinkler by Little Tikes: A combination
sprinkler/water ballgame. Looks like a lot of fun for younger kids,
say 8 and younger. Suggested retail price: $12.99.
</P>
<P>
   4. Storm: Tsunami Force 5 by Trendmasters: This sleek-looking
water gun has lights that turn the water stream into ``liquid
lightning.'' We're not so sure about that _ but it is a great
option for hot summer evenings. You'll need two AA batteries.
Etoys.com priced this toy at $44.99, so if you see it on sale, grab
it.
</P>
<P>
   5. Sesame Street Elmo 1-2-3 Sprinkler by Fisher Price: Here's
one for the littlest kids. There's a mist setting that will keep
babies cool, a gentle stream setting for toddlers and a spinning
setting for preschoolers. Suggested retail price: $17.99.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
