u f BC-ABRAMS-STEWART-NYT &LR;      08-02 0309
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ABRAMS-STEWART-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ILLUSTRATED BOOK PUBLISHERS REACH ACQUISITION DEAL 
</HEADLINE>
   By DAVID D. KIRKPATRICK   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Harry N. Abrams Inc. agreed to pay about $6 million to acquire
the assets of Stewart, Tabori &AMP; Chang, combining two prominent
publishers of illustrated books.
</P>
<P>
   Abrams, a unit of the French publishing concern La Martiniere
Groupe, is one of the largest independent illustrated book
publishers in the United States. The company specializes in art and
art history books, like a recent two-volume photograph collection,
``African Ceremonies.''
</P>
<P>
   Stewart, Tabori &AMP; Chang was founded 20 years ago by former
Abrams executives, including Andrew Stewart, the former husband of
the publisher and television personality Martha Stewart.
</P>
<P>
   Stewart, Tabori &AMP; Chang specializes in coffee-table books about
consumer subjects like cooking, decorating and gardening, as well
as popular art books like the recent Blue Dog series.
</P>
<P>
   Paul Gottlieb, chief executive of Abrams, said the acquisition
would broaden its business into more consumer books, which it could
also profitably sell overseas through its parent company's French
and German units. ``We admire their attitude towards style and
presentation,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Abrams' acquisition also includes Golden Turtle Press, a
calendar publisher with licenses to publish calendars featuring
characters from Star Wars, the World Wildlife Fund and the HBO
television series ``The Sopranos.''
</P>
<P>
   U.S. Media Holdings, based in New York, acquired Stewart, Tabori
&AMP; Chang five years ago and this spring filed for Chapter 11
bankruptcy in New York. In February, the company listed assets of
$24.7 million and liabilities of $25 million.
</P>
<P>
   The bankruptcy court this week approved Abrams' bid for Stewart,
Tabori &AMP; Chang. The deal is expected to be completed next week.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
