   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   HEAT _ Think it's hot enough to fry an egg on the sidewalk?
Well, no, it's not. Though we tried. The raw egg, cracked crisply
into a puddle of canola oil on the sidewalk, just kind of
languished there without frying, sizzling or even sputtering once.
If you've been outside lately, where the temperature's been boiling
up to a hundred degrees or so, you can identify with that egg. Just
wanting to languish there. Too wiped out to even sputter. we also
try. (Grand Junction Daily Sentinel). 30. MOVED.
</P>
