<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE BUSINESS BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These business stories for release Thursday, August 3, 2000, are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   Stories are moving in the financial (f) category. Stories also
moving in lifestyle will be marked with (f, l).
</P>
<P>
   Separate budgets move daily with spot news, features, sports and
commentary.
</P>
<P>
   If you have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the
Cox News Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   BREWER-EARTHLINK _ EarthLink Inc., the No. 2 U.S. Internet
service provider, said Chairman Charles Brewer resigned and will be
replaced by Sky Dayton, who formerly held the position. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DELL-STOCK _ Company stock off about 25 percent from high on
fears about earnings and analysts' downgrades. (Pletz, Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
