</P>
<P>
   GOP-SCHLAFLY (Philadelphia) _ During four decades as a
high-profile Republican activist, Phyllis Schlafly has made it her
vocation to stand athwart what seemed to be irreversible historical
trends, and cry: ``Stop!'' Wednesday, at a lunch with nearly 1,000
paying guests, Schlafly basked in her latest victory _ a Republican
Platform 2000 that maintains word-for-word the anti-abortion
language adopted by the GOP in 1984, 1988, 1992 and 1996.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-FAA (Seattle) _ The Federal Aviation Administration on
Wednesday proposed to fine The Boeing Co. $1.24 million _ the
biggest penalty in Boeing history _ for failing to report problems
with active aircraft and quality control in manufacturing. These
involve incidents that happened some time ago, and the fine is not
related to a recent special audit of Boeing's various manufacturing
problems.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
