   (NYT37) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 2, 2000 -- GOP-BUSH-4 -- A single
spotlight shines on Republican presidential candidate Gov. George
W. Bush during a walk-through on the stage of the Republican
National Convention prior to the evening's session, Wednesday. .
(Suzanne DeChillo/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT36) PHILADELPHIA -- Aug. 2, 2000 -- GOP-FLA-MACK -- Sen.
Connie Mack, R-Fla., is as big a name in Philadelphia as it is in
Florida, so it is fitting that the retiring Florida senator is
spending his last convention hurrah in the city of his birth. Mack
talks with Joe Vento, owner of Geno's Steaks in Philadelphia,
during a luncheon for Senate canidate Bill McCollum on Wednesday.
(Dede Smith/The Gaineville Sun)
</P>
